Welcome back Warriors! Just wanted to share again a quick guide with links to help answer basic questions for the first day of school.

1) Our main office is open from 8:00 am to 3:00 pm. You may reach us at 651-209-8002

2) Questions about technology? Can't log into your chromebook or schoology? Click on this link here: https://www.hcpak12.org/Page/1366

3) Want to learn more about Schoology? Click this link to learn more: https://sites.google.com/apps-hcpak12.org/basicsofschoology/home?pli=1&authuser=1&fbclid=IwAR1QCrecIaWUUPbW1NAS4jZ8V9PhO6IMlnC7HfF7tWbxxy2llUHpi4MG7k8

4) Free Lunch distribution for ALL K-12 Students tomorrow Tuesday Sept 8, from 10am - 2pm. Please drive up and pickup at Door B! No phone call necessary!

5) What are your roles and responsibilities as a student/parent during Distance Learning? Click here to learn more: https://www.hcpak12.org/Page/1369

post_text:
HCPA Parents, Students, and Staff,

With the 2019-2020 school year behind us, Hmong College Prep Academy would appreciate your feedback on the end of our spring distance learning. Currently, we are awaiting guidance from the Minnesota Department of Education and the State of Minnesota on how we will be expected to start school in the fall. Your feedback will be helpful as we reflect on how to move forward to best support the education of all our K-12 students.

Parents, students, and staff in K-12 may complete the following survey: http://tiny.cc/zneqqz

Parents are also encouraged to complete an additional survey to give feedback to the Minnesota Department of Education on distance learning: http://sgiz.mobi/s3/2020-Parent-Distance-Learning-Feedback-Survey

Thank you for your collaboration and support. Have a wonderful summer!

Final Call: HCPA Senior Photo Opportunity. This event will take place Monday June 22nd from 2-4 PM. We have time slots still available, please call our main office at 651-209-8002 to schedule before the event starts!

**When you arrive, please remain in your car and follow detailed instructions from staff. Please be ready, with your full graduation gown, and cap.

You may also choose to email us a photo of your student in their cap and gown. Please send this to tony.hang@hcpak12.org by Tuesday June 23, 2020 4:00 PM.

If you do not send us a photo, we will use your most recent school photo.

Thank you

HCPA Administration are asking families to follow the 8 pm curfew set by our Mayor Melvin Carter (STP), and Governor Tim Walz.

"The temporary curfew is in place from 8 p.m. Sunday to 6 a.m. Monday. During the curfew, no one is allowed to travel on Minneapolis and Saint Paul streets or public places, except for first responders, members of the media, people going back and forth to work, individuals seeking emergency care or fleeing danger, and people experiencing homelessness." MN.gov

post_text:
K-2 Work Packet Pick-Up
Hello Kindergarten, First, and Second Grade Families,

On Thursday, April 23rd, Governor Walz directed all Minnesota schools to continue distance learning through the end of the school year. With this announcement, we are planning to distribute our next round of HCPA Distance Learning Packets for all kindergarten through 2nd grade students. These new and improved packets will keep your child engaged in distance learning through June 4th.

Packet pick up will be Monday, April 27th from 10:00 am – 2:00 pm. We will be distributing from the field house attached to the dome. HCPA will follow strict safety precautions to ensure families and staff members stay safe and healthy.

Questions?

Contact Krista Skoglund at 651-231-3960 or Mariah Mercil at 651-424-6966.

Need a Hmong interpreter? Call the main office at 651-209-8002.

Need a Karen interpreter? Call Saw Lu Lu at 651-703-8324.

Tonight, Monday, April 6th, to honor all HCPA students, staff, and especially the 2020 senior class, HCPA will be joining other schools from across the state in the #BeTheLightMN movement. Our sports dome lights will be flipped on tonight at 8:20 pm for 20 minutes and 20 seconds (20:20).

We miss you all, but ask that you enjoy the lights from afar. If you do decide to visit the school, we ask that you drive by and/or park. Please refrain from getting out of your vehicles.

A great way to participate from home is to put a light in your front window, porch, deck, balcony at 8:20 pm for 20:20. If you do, please take a picture and send it to Schoology@hcpak12.org so we can put together a collage!!

<3 Chi You

post_text:
Reference Map for Monday and Tuesday! Remain in your Vehicles, and please review the layout.
REMINDER:
• Chromebooks and learning materials for K-5 will be available for pick up next week.
• Monday, March 23rd will be pickup for students who have a last name that starts with A-U.
• Tuesday, March 24th will be pickup for students who have a last name that starts with V-Z.
• Hours for pickup on both days will be 9:00-noon and 1:00-3:00.
• All resources will be brought out to your vehicle for you.
• When you arrive, please enter the parking lot across from the Main Office C. There will be staff members directing traffic. Please review the included map.
• A parent or guardian must be present to check out the resources. For 3rd-5th grade students, we will go over the Chromebook contract with you at that time. You will have the option to purchase insurance for the device to protect against potential damage.
• If you are a high schooler or middle schooler and you left something in your locker, you may also come during this time. Someone will retrieve your items for you.

post_text:
HCPA Students and Families: The staff at Hmong College Prep Academy are continuing their work in preparing for long term distance learning.

The current plan is to proceed with 3rd-12th grade online classes starting AFTER Spring Break ends on April 6th. Plans are being developed to ensure access to computers and internet for all students. K-2 teachers are also developing plans to ensure as little disruption to the learning process as possible.

These plans are fluid, and subject to change. We will keep you updated as the situation requires.

Thank you all for your patience as we make our way through this unprecedented situation.

All Hmong College Prep Academy classes and activities are canceled Monday, March 16 and Tuesday, March 17, because we are beginning to implement mitigation strategies to help slow the spread of the Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19).

Important Message to all Parents, Guardians and Students,

The safety of the faculty, staff, and students of Hmong College Prep Academy is the primary factor when making decisions about early school release. Although our first preference is to keep our standard release time, there are times when it is necessary to release students early.

Hmong College Prep Academy will be releasing students early from school on Friday January 17, 2020 at 1:00 pm due to predicted inclement weather.

Please make the necessary arrangements to have someone home to open house doors for your child(ren) as needed.

To learn more about our School Cancelled for Inclement Weather Policy, please refer to our website at www.hcpak12.org

post_text: Last night was the annual University of St. Thomas High School Honor Band day, where they offered an exceptional program of rehearsing with an internationally renowned conductor: Dario Sotelo, small group instruction on their instrument, a tour of the St. Thomas campus, along with performing in a concert at the end of the day. This is a very prestigious event with students from all over the state participating. With that said, 4 of our HCPA Honors Band students were nominated and accepted to perform! These students are Skyler Xiong (11), Mathyus Yang (11), Maung Nine Paw (10), and Andy Thao (9).

post_text:
Hello Families of HCPA,
Our first day of school will be Tuesday, September 3. We wanted to remind all students about our school uniform policy. Letters have been sent home and you may also review our uniform guide on our website. Uniforms can be purchased at HCPA between the hours of 7am-3:30pm Monday thru Friday.

A reminder for transportation as well. Buses may run late due to the first day of school. We recommend watching "Bus Status" on our website, or you may download the app onto your phone. We need all students to be at the designated stop 5 minutes early, and be visual. All house stops are required to stand outside of their house.

For all new or kindergarten students, we recommend writing a small letter with their identification. Tags were sent home to all Kindergarten students.

See you all soon.

Thank you so much everyone!!! We will grow and become stronger in the future!!!!💗
